        <h2>2-1) How do I add a new member?</h2>

<p>If the member is part of a household already subscribed to GROW, you have to ask for their household information first. Once you have it, click on the households tab on the sidebar. You will be prompted with a table of all the households registered in our 
database. On the last column of every row, you will see action icons to edit the household information, to see the household information in more detail and also to 
add a new member to it straight away.</p> 

<p>Click on the green perfon icon to add a new member to that household.</p>

<p>If a member is not part of a household subscribed to GROW, you will have to enter their household information first.</p> 

<p>To create a membership, click on the households tab on the sidebar. On the households index page, click on the Create New button at the top. 
You will be prompted with a form to create a new household. After you fill in the Household information, you will be presented to add a new member to your newly 
created membership.</p>

<h2>2-2) How do I change members' informations?</h2>

<p>To change member's information you can do it two ways.</p>

<p>Click on the households tab on the sidebar. Over there, you will see a button called Member's Index. There you will see a table of all members of GROW and in the last
column of all rows, you will see a group of action icons. Click on the grey pencil icon to navigate to the edit page. Over there, you can edit the selected member
information.</p>

<p>Alternatively, you can navigate to the member's household in the Households Index and click the corresponding blue 'i' icon to go to the Household Details page. From 
there, you will see a list of the household's members in a table near the top of the page. From here, click the green 'Edit' button next to the member whose details 
you would like to change, and you will be brought to the Edit Member page where you can do so.</p>

<h2>2-3) How do I see a member's details?</h2> 

<p>There are two ways to find a member's details.</p>

<p>Click on the Households tab on the sidebar. Here you will see a button called Members Index. Click that and you will be brought to the Members Index page, where you 
can find every member registered in the GROW database and search for the one you need by pressing the grey 'Filter/Sort' button. From here, click the blue 'i' icon 
next to the member whose details you want to view and you will be brought to their details page. </p>

<p>Alternatively, you can navigate to the member's household in the Households Index and click on the corresponding blue 'i' icon to go to that household's Details page. 
On this details page you will find a list of member's belonging to the household. Click on the blue-highlighted name of the member you want to view and you will be 
brought directly to their details page.</p>

<h2>2-4) How do I delete a member?</h2>

<p>There are two ways to accomplish this task.</p>

<p>Click on the Households tab on the sidebar. Here you will see a button called Members Index. Click that and you will be brought to the Members Index page, where you 
can find every member registered in the GROW database and search for the one you need by pressing the grey 'Filter/Sort' button. From here, click the red circle icon. 
This will bring you to a confirmation screen where you can view the member's details and make sure that you want to delete them. On this page, you can click the red 
Delete button at the bottom to follow through and delete them from the system, or the grey Cancel and go back to the previous page without deleting the member.</p>

<p>Alternatively, you may also delete a member from the Household Details page much the same way as you can edit them. Go to the Households button on the side bar and 
click it, then find the household that the member you are looking to delete belongs to. Click the corresponding blue 'i' button to navigate to the Household Details 
page. From here, locate the member you wish to delete in the upper Household Members table and click the red Delete button. Again, this will bring you to a member 
details page where you may confirm or cancel the deletion. </p>

<h2>2-5) There are a lot of members. How can I find the one I'm looking for?</h2>

<p>Due to the naturally large number of members being dealt with, it has been made exceptionally easy to locate a specific member in the system and there are two ways to do this.</p>

<p>Navigate to the Households Index via the Households button on the side bar, then click the blue Members Index button near the top of the page. Once on the Members 
Index page, click the grey 'Filter/Sort' button near the top and you will be presented with a number of different options. From here you will be able to search by 
Member Name, Phone Number, Household Address, Household ID, Gender, or any combination of the above.</p>

<p>If you want, you can also navigate directly to the household that the member belongs to on the Households Index page if you know it and select the blue 'i' icon next 
to it. Here you can see all members belonging to that household, including the one you are looking for.</p>
      </div>
