        <h2>3-1) How do I create a new order?</h2> 

<p>Click on the Orders button on the sidebar, represented by a shopping cart icon, and you will be brought to a page listing every order that has been placed in the 
system. Click on the green 'Create New' button near the top of the page. You will now need to enter two things. First, enter the Household ID and click the grey 
'Search' button. From here you will be prompted to select a member. Select the member placing the order and click the green 'Create' button to be brought to the New 
Order page.</p>

<p>On this page you can add items to the order by pressing the green '+' button under the Order Information section. This will create a popup prompting you to select an 
item from a dropdown list as well as the quantity of the item being purchased. Make the appropriate selections for the purchase being made and click the grey 'Create' 
button to add this item to the order. Repeat this process for each item the member wishes to purchase. </p>

<p>Once you have added all of the member's selected items to the Order Information section, you are going to want to turn your eyes to the top right area of the page. 
Here you should find a section titled 'Pay and Submit' where you can select the payment method being used for the transaction. Once you have made the appropriate 
selection from the dropdown menu, click the green 'Create' button to finish entering the order into the system. </p>

<p>3-2) I made a mistake in creating a new order. Can I go back and fix it? </p>

<p>Yes! To edit any order, navigate to the Orders Index from the Orders button on the sidebar. From here, click the grey pencil icon next to the order you want to edit 
and you'll be brought back to the same screen you used to add items and select payment type in the first place.</p>

<h2>3-3) What if I want to delete an order?</h2>

<p>You can delete orders by navigating to the Orders Index via the Orders button on the sidebar. From here, simply find the order you need to delete and click the red 
circle icon next to it. You will then be brought to a summary page to review the order being deleted. You can now click the red 'Delete' button to continue with 
deleting the order, the 'Back to Orders' button to return to the previous page, or the 'Back to Member' button to view the details of the member whose purchase you are 
currently looking at.</p>

<h2>3-4) How can I quickly find a specific order in the system?</h2>

<p>To quickly find any order, all you need to do is navigate to the Orders page via the sidebar and then click the grey 'Filter/Search' button near the top of the page, 
under 'Create New'. This will expand a menu which lets you search orders by Household Name or ID, Member, and Payment Type. Once you have entered the appropriate 
information, click the green 'Submit' button and the table below will display only orders that meet these criteria.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
