        <h2>4-1) What if the item I need isn't in the system?</h2>

<p>First of all, this operation is restricted to administrators only. To add a new item to the GROW system, find the Items button on the sidebar, represented by a book icon. This will bring you to the Items Index where you can find every 
item currently in the GROW system and perform a number of different operations on them. From here, click the green 'Create New' button near the top of the page to 
navigate to the Item Creation page.</p>

<p>Here, you will be prompted for an Item Code, Name, Description, Price, Discount Percentage, and Category. All of these fields are required except Discount and 
Description, so fill these out appropriately to match the item you wish to add. Once you have filled out the form, click the green 'Create' button at the bottom to add 
the item to the system and return to the Items Index.</p>

<h2>4-2) How do I edit an item that's already been created?</h2>

<p>Navigate to the Items Index via the Items button on the sidebar, and find the item you want to edit in the list. Once you have found the item you want to edit, click 
the grey pencil icon to navigate to the Edit Item page. Here you can change any of the item's details including its Item Code.</p>

<h2>4-3) How can I apply a discount to an item? How do I remove a discount?</h2>

<p>To add or remove a discount from any item, navigate to the Items Index and click the grey pencil icon next to the item you want to change. On this Edit Item page, you 
can change the 'Discount (%)' field to represent the discount (or lack thereof) you wish to apply to that item.</p>

<h2>4-4) How can I quickly find a specific item?</h2>

<p>Like most other indexes, it is possible to filter by a variety of fields to find the item you need. First, navigate to the Items Index via the Items button on the 
sidebar. From here, click the grey 'Filter/Search' button near the top and take note of the fields you can search by. Once you have entered the relevant information 
you wish to search/filter by, click the green 'Filter' button and the table below will reflect your specifications.</p>
