        <h2>5-1) What is the Misc Data tab for on the side bar? </h2>

<p>The Misc Tab is there so that administrators can add or remove "lookup values" within the app. Lookup values are essentially anything you might find in a dropdown list 
that isn't prone to changing any time soon. The dietary restrictions and payment type selections are examples of this. Essentially, they exist to allow for flexibility 
and growth of the application over time to suit the needs of the user.</p>

<h2>5-2) How can I change or add lookup values?</h2>

<h3>-- Add</h3>
<p>All tabs in the Lookup Values page will have the same options asides from Notification Types which has an extra option for sending a notification. To add a value to 
the lookups, select which one you would like to add to, Cities for example, and click the 'Create' button near the bottom left of the window. You will be prompted to 
enter a city name. Click the green 'Create' button after filling in the Name field and that city will be added to the lookup values for City.</p>

<h3>-- Edit</h3>
<p>If you want to edit a value, click on the item you want to edit in the list and it should be highlighted. Now, click the 'Edit' button near the bottom left of the 
screen. This will bring you to an Edit page where you can change the name of your selected lookup value.</p>

<h3>-- Delete</h3>
<p>If you want to delete a value altogether, click on the item you want to delete from the list and it should be highlighted. Now, click the 'Delete' button near the 
bottom of the screen alongside the other action buttons. You will be asked if you're sure that you want to delete the selected item, which you can confirm by clicking 
the red 'Delete' button or back out of by clicking 'Back to Lookup List'.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
