        <h2>6-1) Who can assign roles?</h2>

<p>For security reasons, only the Super Administrator is able to assign roles to volunteers of GROW. </p>

<h2>6-2) Can a Super Administrator change their own role?</h2>

<p>No. This would make it possible to have NO Super Administrators at a given time meaning that no roles could ever be assigned again.</p>

<h2>6-3) Can there be multiple Super Administrators and Admins? </h2>

<p>Yes, there can be as many of each role as the organization sees fit. </p>

<h2>6-4) How do I create a new user?</h2>

<p>While logged in as the Super Administrator, go down to the Employees tab on the sidebar. Click it and you will be brought to the Employees Index, listing all current 
employees. Next, click 'Create New Employee' near the top of the page. Once on the Register Employee page, fill out all the necessary and required fields. New users 
will automatically be assigned the lowest User role but can be assigned greater privileges after the fact.</p>

<h2>6-5) Can I disable a user login?</h2>

<p>Yes you can. As a Super Administrator, navigate to the Employees Index via the sidebar and click the 'Edit' button corresponding to the user you wish to disable. You 
will be brought to an Edit page where you can edit their information. From here, un-check the 'Active' checkbox. Be warned, however, that unchecking this will force 
that user to re-register their email with the GROW system after checking it again.</p>
